From: jem@snakemail.hut.fi (Johan Myreen)
Subject: Re: [Q] dos2unix for Linux,where
Date: 28 Sep 93 14:20:12 GMT

In article <KWH.93Sep27110633@vegas.cs.brown.edu> kwh@cs.brown.edu (Kwun Han) writes:
>In article <CDzzv1.M5M@iupui.edu> jmadison@etsun.tech.iupui.edu (Gold Silver Soup and Silk) writes:

>   where could i get sources (binary) for dos2unix for Linux? 
>   thanx.

>Could always write your own. takes less than 30 lines of code.

Or, assuming the file to be converted comes from a DOS partition, one
possibility is to mount the partition with the mount option
'-o conv=text' or '-o conv=auto'. No lines of code required.
This won't work on tar'ed or zipped files, of course...

